item.title: What is better?
item.dc:creator: @Liquid_Magic Liquid Magic
item.description:
@Liquid_Magic wrote:

[quote=“Uncalled, post:13, topic:369769”][quote author=Liquid Magic link=topic=465893.msg3410884#msg3410884 date=1290673496]

317 Delta is about 50000% easier then any other sevrer.
[/quote]Java is Java. You cannot label it by the client’s cache revision, nor the server’s login protocol. It will still be Java, no matter what base you use.

So you’ll tell me, when you’ve coded only for about a month, and you think coding a Hyperion is just as easy as a Delta?

That is necessarily true. Hyperion is just as easy to program than any other server out there. I just support it because it has all the things that I don’t want to do. Anyone could turn Delta Scape into a runner-up for a Hyperion.

If you’ve only coded for a mere month, so new to coding, and Hyperion is just as easy as Delta? Brand new to coding?[/quote]

It wouldn’t matter. The only thing that may surprise anyone new to Hyperion is just the rather different packaging (which is a lot more professional, and easier to deal with), it’s not all in one tree;). And my advice to anyone who is new to programming would not to be starting of developing a fucking game.

Read full topic
